info.headline: High Wind Warning issued March 19 at 12:12PM MDT until March 20 at 12:00AM MDT by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT MDT TONIGHT... * WHAT...West to southwest winds 35 to 50 MPH with gusts up to 60 MPH possible. * WHERE...North Snowy Range Foothills including Arlington and Elk Mountain along Interstate 80 between Laramie and Rawlins, Central Laramie Range and southwest Platte County including Bordeaux along Interstate 25 between Chugwater and Wheatland. * WHEN...Now until Midnight MDT tonight. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
